Great recipe. Even easier method: Add scant ¼ c. flour to oven (cooking) bag. Mix in ingredients. Place brisket in bag (no browning necessary!). Cut slits on top of bag. Bake in 300° oven 3 ½ hours or more (or until fork tender). Skim fat (best is to chill overnight). What could be easier?

