I haven't made this specific recipe per se, but it's almost identical to my personal creation, which always gets rave reviews. Try using ginger ale instead of the beer, and a package of Knorr's or Mrs. Grass onion soup mix. Also, I use a good quality pasta sauce, such as Barilla, instead of ketchup - just 1/3 cup. Before searing, coating just with paprika (no added salt or pepper required). It's heaven.

