I can't believe how easy and delicious this recipe was. Don't be put off by the sauce when you first mix it -- I was a little nervous because it was very foamy and tasted a little weird. I used two smaller briskets (about 5 lbs. total weight), doubled the sauce and onions, and left it in the oven for four hours. Oh, and be sure to use a good, really heavy Dutch oven with a tight-fitting lid so the liquid doesn't evaporate. The meat came out falling-apart tender and the sauce was luscious. Leftovers tasted even better. This was the best brisket recipe I've ever made.

